I have encountered a major issue while deploying my game to the iOS platform via RoboVM.

The problem:
Whenever I pause my app ( and this could be done by pressing the home button or switching over to Facebook after clicking the share or app invite buttons) and then resume it, I am left with a blank screen, as if my classes have disappeared. After doing some debugging I found that it is not a problem of my AssetLoader. I think it is caused by the lack of proper storing when the app pauses and then resumes.
This problem even occurs when there is some lagging (in my simulator for example), so I believe it is related to the lifecycle.

This is not an issue of the Android version.

