Hey guys, I am almost done creating my first game, however, I have run into some problems on the iOS version. i use FitViewport for each of my Screens, but it doesn't seem to dothe job. The code below works perfect on Desktop and Android.
#### Issue details

i use a class called Renderer to initialize the elements for resizing, and I call them in the resize method of the Screen class. 
#### Reproduction steps/code

```
camera = new OrthographicCamera(MenuScreen.VIRTUAL_WIDTH,
            MenuScreen.VIRTUAL_HEIGHT);
viewport = new FitViewport(MenuScreen.VIRTUAL_WIDTH,
            MenuScreen.VIRTUAL_HEIGHT, camera);
viewport.apply();
camera.position.set(camera.viewportWidth / 2,
            camera.viewportHeight / 2, 0);
b = new SpriteBatch();
b.setProjectionMatrix(camera.combined);
```

```
@Override
public void resize(int width, int height) {
    renderer.getViewport().update(width, height);
    renderer.camera.position.set(renderer.camera.viewportWidth / 2,
            renderer.camera.viewportHeight / 2, 0);
    renderer.getB().setProjectionMatrix(renderer.getCamera().combined);

}

```

